# TypeScript Strict

- No implicit `any` — enable strict checks; `tsconfig.app.json` has `"strict": true`
- No non-null assertions (`!`) unless justified with an inline comment explaining why
- Prefer type inference inside function bodies; **always** type function params and return values at boundaries
- Use discriminated unions for async/UI state — e.g. `status: 'idle' | 'loading' | 'error' | 'success'` — never parallel `isLoading` + `isError` + `isSuccess` booleans
- Derive types from Zod schemas via `z.infer<typeof Schema>` — do not hand-write duplicate interfaces

## Exports

- **Named exports** everywhere except:
  - Page route components (lazy-loaded from feature barrels)
  - `src/app/App.tsx` (default export)
  - `vite.config.ts` (default export)
- Never use `export default` for hooks, utils, API functions, or shared components

## `any` escape hatch

Only with inline comment: `// any: <reason>`
